    "body": "> Is it blurry because of using a non retina PNG? SVG could be a solution\n\nSo first it's blurry indeed, but mostly it's not the current/latest version of the logo /o\\\n\nI kept the same PNG format for now. Maybe base64/inlined SVG is working as well -> I think we went for PNG to target old IE browsers (https://css-tricks.com/probably-dont-base64-svg/#article-header-id-1).\n",
